// =============================================================================
// core.action.monads — concrete strong-monad implementations (VVA-9 V1)
// =============================================================================
//
// Concrete data-type-and-impl pairs for each effect declared in
// `core.action.effects` per Theorem 17.T1 (effects ≃ Perf(α_linear)
// projections via Kleisli embedding). The protocol surface lives in
// `core.action.effects`; this module ships the witness data types.
//
// V1 scope (this module): the four most-used monads — `Pure` (identity),
// `Reader<R, A>` (env-reading), `Writer<W, A>` (append-only output),
// and `State<S, A>` (mutable cell). Together they cover:
//
//   • the canonical commutative monads (`Pure`, `Reader`, `Writer`)
//     that compose under @verify(coherent_concurrent) per Theorem 17.C2;
//   • the canonical non-commutative monad (`State`) that DOES NOT
//     compose under coherent-concurrent without explicit
//     synchronisation — used by VVA §11.2 to demonstrate the gate.
//
// V1.5 partial — `Probability` (commit history) and `Exception` (this
// commit) are now wired with full monad-law theorems. Remaining V1.5
// gaps: `List` (commutative non-determinism) and `Io` (canonical
// real-world side-effect monad). V2 will lift the monad-laws from
// V1 trusted-boundary axioms to `@verify(formal)`-discharged proofs.
//
// Each monad ships:
//   - data type with the canonical Kleisli shape;
//   - `pure` / `bind` / `strength` standalone functions
//     (protocol-implementation form pending VVA §11.5 protocol-impl
//     syntax landing for parameterised types);
//   - three monad-law axioms (left identity / right identity /
//     associativity).
// =============================================================================

public mount core.action.monads.pure;
public mount core.action.monads.reader;
public mount core.action.monads.writer;
public mount core.action.monads.state;
// VVA-Tier-A V0 — probabilistic + quantum effect classes.
public mount core.action.monads.probability;
public mount core.action.monads.quantum;
// VVA-Tier-A V1.5 — short-circuiting failure monad (non-commutative,
// ε-coordinate ω + 1 alongside State / Io).
public mount core.action.monads.exception;
